# Quality gates (product repo)

Agents MUST NOT claim work is complete without running applicable checks on the **combined** working tree after coordinator synthesis.

## By path

| Paths | Command |
| --- | --- |
| `backend/**` (routes, middleware, lib) | Unit tests + `./bin/smoke-local.sh` |
| HTTP contract changes | Update `swagger-ui/openapi.yaml` in same PR |
| `electricity-prices-build/**` | Frontend lint/test per project CI |
| Migrations | Sequential numbered SQL; no duplicate migration numbers |
| `bin/*.sh`, `*.sh` | `bash -n <file>` |
| New golden scenario | Add under `tests/golden/`; run in CI or locally |

## Coordinator integration gate

When a coordinator merges work from multiple subagents, MUST re-run applicable rows above on the **merged tree** before spawning the ship subagent.

## PR discipline

- Title: `[scope] <short description>`
- Body: test plan checklist with commands actually run
- Reference GitHub issue (`Fixes #N` or `Refs #N`)
- One unit, one PR for solo work; coordinator multi-issue slices MAY use one combined PR when PO listed parallel issues

## Security

- MUST NOT commit `.env`, `local.env`, credentials, or `node_modules/`
- Reference secret **names** in docs, never values
- Run `security-review` subagent when MUST triggers in AGENTS.md apply

## Contributing reference

Product repos do not install flows [CONTRIBUTING.md](https://github.com/alicemq/flows/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md). Use this repo's `AGENTS.md` and checklists under `docs/checklists/`.
